Banyana Banyana Coach, Desiree Ellis won the Sport Lifetime Community Award at the Hollard Sport Industry Awards. She talks to Nicole Kente #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Banyana-Banyana coach, Desiree Ellis has been honoured this week for her feeding scheme. The 57-year-old unanimously won the Sports Lifetime Community Award at the Hollard Sport Industry Awards. "We never do things for awards or rewards," says Ellis. READ:Â Banyana Banyana bag another Cosafa Women's Championship title "All I am trying to do is make a difference in my community," she says Ellis' foundation provides up to 600 meals in and around Hanover Park in the Cape Flats in Cape Town. For more, watch the interview above. 